{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Mt35JSKuvWXCAh3fWVqtcV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 13-3: Migrate run.ts to Use AgentDriver\n     2→\n     3→## Status: review\n     4→\n     5→<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n     6→\n     7→<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->\n     8→\n     9→## Story\n    10→\n    11→As a developer,\n    12→I want `run.ts` to use `AgentDriver` instead of directly spawning Ralph,\n    13→So that the run command is agent-agnostic.\n    14→\n    15→## Acceptance Criteria\n    16→\n    17→1. Given `src/commands/run.ts`, when inspected, then it does NOT import `spawn` from `node:child_process` — all process spawning goes through `AgentDriver.spawn()` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→2. Given `src/commands/run.ts`, when inspected, then it imports a `getDriver()` factory from `../lib/agents/index.js` and calls `driver.spawn(opts)` where `driver` is an `AgentDriver` instance <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19→3. Given `src/commands/run.ts`, when inspected, then it does NOT import or call `buildSpawnArgs()` or `resolveRalphPath()` directly — those are encapsulated inside `RalphDriver.spawn()` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20→4. Given `src/commands/run.ts`, when inspected, then it replaces the inline `createLineProcessor` stderr/stdout wiring with `driver.parseOutput(line)` calls that return `AgentEvent` objects, and a `handleAgentEvent()` dispatcher function that updates the Ink renderer <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    21→5. Given `src/commands/run.ts`, when inspected, then the hardcoded `'ralph/status.json'` path is replaced with `driver.getStatusFile()` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    22→6. Given `src/lib/agents/index.ts`, when inspected, then it exports a `getDriver(name?: string): AgentDriver` factory function that returns a `RalphDriver` instance by default and throws for unknown driver names <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    23→7. Given `RalphDriver.spawn()`, when called, then it internally calls `resolveRalphPath()` and `buildSpawnArgs()` — the `SpawnOpts` interface carries enough information for `RalphDriver` to construct all ralph.sh flags (the interface or `spawn()` signature may need extending to pass `pluginDir`, `maxIterations`, `iterationTimeout`, `calls`, `quiet`, `maxStoryRetries`, `reset`) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    24→8. Given `src/commands/run.ts` re-exports `countStories` and `buildSpawnArgs`, when migration completes, then `buildSpawnArgs` and `resolveRalphPath` are no longer re-exported from `run.ts` (they are implementation details of `RalphDriver`) — `countStories` may still be re-exported if external consumers need it <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    25→9. Given `src/lib/run-helpers.ts`, when inspected, then `createLineProcessor` is either removed (if no longer used) or remains as a backward-compatible utility — run.ts itself must NOT use it <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    26→10. Given `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts`, when inspected, then it tests the run command through the `AgentDriver` interface: mocking `getDriver()` to return a mock driver, verifying `driver.spawn()` is called with correct opts, and verifying `driver.parseOutput()` events are dispatched to the renderer <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    27→11. Given `npm run build` runs after all changes, then TypeScript compilation succeeds with zero errors <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    28→12. Given `npm test` runs after all changes, then all existing tests pass with zero regressions <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    29→13. Given no file in `src/lib/agents/` or `src/commands/`, when line count is checked, then no file exceeds 300 lines <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    30→\n    31→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    32→\n    33→- [x] Task 1 (AC: 7): Extend `RalphDriver.spawn()` to accept full run configuration\n    34→  - [x]Extend `SpawnOpts` or add a `RalphSpawnOpts` that includes `pluginDir`, `maxIterations`, `iterationTimeout`, `calls`, `quiet`, `maxStoryRetries`, `reset` fields needed by `buildSpawnArgs()`\n    35→  - [x]Update `RalphDriver.spawn()` to use these new fields instead of hardcoded defaults (currently hardcodes `maxIterations: 50`, `iterationTimeout: 30`, `calls: 100`, `quiet: false`)\n    36→  - [x]Ensure `resolveRalphPath()` is called internally by `spawn()` — the caller should NOT need to know about `ralph.sh`\n    37→\n    38→- [x] Task 2 (AC: 6): Add `getDriver()` factory to `src/lib/agents/index.ts`\n    39→  - [x]Implement `getDriver(name?: string): AgentDriver` — defaults to `'ralph'`, returns `new RalphDriver()`\n    40→  - [x]Throw a descriptive error for unrecognized driver names (e.g., `Unknown agent driver: ${name}`)\n    41→  - [x]Export `getDriver` from the barrel\n    42→\n    43→- [x] Task 3 (AC: 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 8, 9): Refactor `src/commands/run.ts`\n    44→  - [x]Remove `import { spawn } from 'node:child_process'`\n    45→  - [x]Remove `import { buildSpawnArgs, resolveRalphPath } from '../lib/agents/ralph.js'`\n    46→  - [x]Add `import { getDriver } from '../lib/agents/index.js'`\n    47→  - [x]Add `import type { AgentDriver, AgentEvent } from '../lib/agents/types.js'`\n    48→  - [x]Replace `const ralphPath = resolveRalphPath(); if (!existsSync(ralphPath))` check with driver validation (the driver itself knows if its executable exists)\n    49→  - [x]Replace `const args = buildSpawnArgs(...)` + `spawn('bash', args, ...)` with `const driver = getDriver(); const child = driver.spawn(opts)`\n    50→  - [x]Create a `handleAgentEvent(event: AgentEvent, rendererHandle)` function that switches on `event.type` and calls appropriate renderer methods (`update`, `addMessage`, etc.)\n    51→  - [x]Replace `createLineProcessor` usage with a line splitter that calls `driver.parseOutput(line)` and dispatches via `handleAgentEvent()`\n    52→  - [x]Replace hardcoded `join(projectDir, 'ralph', 'status.json')` with `join(projectDir, driver.getStatusFile())`\n    53→  - [x]Remove re-exports of `buildSpawnArgs` and `resolveRalphPath` — keep `countStories` re-export\n    54→  - [x]Remove the `// resolveRalphPath moved to ...` comment (now fully encapsulated)\n    55→\n    56→- [x] Task 4 (AC: 10): Update `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts`\n    57→  - [x]Mock `../lib/agents/index.js` to return a mock `AgentDriver` from `getDriver()`\n    58→  - [x]Remove mocks for `node:child_process` `spawn` (no longer directly called by run.ts)\n    59→  - [x]Verify `driver.spawn()` is called with the correct `SpawnOpts` when the run command executes\n    60→  - [x]Verify `driver.parseOutput()` is called for each output line\n    61→  - [x]Verify `driver.getStatusFile()` is used for reading session results\n    62→  - [x]Update any tests that reference `buildSpawnArgs` or `resolveRalphPath` imports from run.ts\n    63→\n    64→- [x] Task 5 (AC: 11): Run `npm run build` — TypeScript compilation succeeds\n    65→- [x] Task 6 (AC: 12): Run `npm test` — all existing tests pass, zero regressions\n    66→- [x] Task 7 (AC: 13): Verify all modified files are under 300 lines\n    67→\n    68→## Dev Notes\n    69→\n    70→### Architecture Compliance\n    71→\n    72→- **Decision 3 (Agent Abstraction):** This is the capstone story of Epic 13. After this, `run.ts` programs exclusively to the `AgentDriver` interface. Swapping Ralph for another agent requires only a new driver implementation and a `getDriver('newagent')` call.\n    73→- **Decision 7 (300-line limit, NFR5):** `run.ts` is currently 282 lines. The refactoring should reduce it slightly (removing inline buildSpawnArgs/resolveRalphPath usage), but the `handleAgentEvent()` function adds some code. Monitor the total.\n    74→\n    75→### Implementation Guidance\n    76→\n    77→**The core change pattern:**\n    78→\n    79→```typescript\n    80→// BEFORE (current run.ts):\n    81→import { spawn } from 'node:child_process';\n    82→import { buildSpawnArgs, resolveRalphPath } from '../lib/agents/ralph.js';\n    83→// ...\n    84→const ralphPath = resolveRalphPath();\n    85→const args = buildSpawnArgs({ ralphPath, pluginDir, promptFile, ... });\n    86→const child = spawn('bash', args, { stdio, cwd, env });\n    87→// ...\n    88→const stdoutHandler = createLineProcessor({ onEvent: ... });\n    89→const stderrHandler = createLineProcessor({ onEvent: ..., onMessage: ..., onIteration: ... }, { parseRalph: true });\n    90→child.stdout.on('data', stdoutHandler);\n    91→child.stderr.on('data', stderrHandler);\n    92→// ...\n    93→const statusFile = join(projectDir, 'ralph', 'status.json');\n    94→\n    95→// AFTER:\n    96→import { getDriver } from '../lib/agents/index.js';\n    97→import type { AgentDriver, AgentEvent } from '../lib/agents/types.js';\n    98→// ...\n    99→const driver = getDriver();\n   100→const child = driver.spawn({ storyKey: '...', prompt: promptFile, workDir: projectDir, timeout, ... });\n   101→// ...\n   102→// Line splitting + driver.parseOutput() + handleAgentEvent()\n   103→// ...\n   104→const statusFile = join(projectDir, driver.getStatusFile());\n   105→```\n   106→\n   107→**SpawnOpts extension challenge:**\n   108→\n   109→The current `SpawnOpts` interface (from 13-1) has: `storyKey`, `prompt`, `workDir`, `timeout`, `env`. But `run.ts` passes many more options to `buildSpawnArgs()`: `pluginDir`, `maxIterations`, `iterationTimeout`, `calls`, `quiet`, `maxStoryRetries`, `reset`.\n   110→\n   111→Options for handling this:\n   112→1. **Extend `SpawnOpts`** with optional ralph-specific fields (violates interface purity)\n   113→2. **Use `env` bag** to pass extra config (hacky)\n   114→3. **Add a `RalphSpawnOpts extends SpawnOpts`** type that `RalphDriver.spawn()` accepts (type-safe, recommended)\n   115→4. **Configure `RalphDriver` at construction time** — pass ralph-specific options to the constructor, leaving `SpawnOpts` generic\n   116→\n   117→Option 3 or 4 is recommended. Option 4 is cleanest: `new RalphDriver(ralphConfig)` at construction, then `driver.spawn(genericOpts)` at call time. This keeps `SpawnOpts` agent-agnostic.\n   118→\n   119→**handleAgentEvent() dispatcher:**\n   120→\n   121→```typescript\n   122→function handleAgentEvent(\n   123→  event: AgentEvent,\n   124→  rendererHandle: RendererHandle,\n   125→  state: { currentIterationCount: number },\n   126→): void {\n   127→  switch (event.type) {\n   128→    case 'tool-start':\n   129→    case 'tool-complete':\n   130→    case 'text':\n   131→    case 'result':\n   132→    case 'retry':\n   133→      // Map to StreamEvent-like shape for renderer.update()\n   134→      rendererHandle.update(event);\n   135→      break;\n   136→    case 'story-complete':\n   137→      rendererHandle.addMessage({ type: 'ok', key: event.key, message: event.details });\n   138→      break;\n   139→    case 'story-failed':\n   140→      rendererHandle.addMessage({ type: 'fail', key: event.key, message: event.reason });\n   141→      break;\n   142→    case 'iteration':\n   143→      state.currentIterationCount = event.count;\n   144→      break;\n   145→  }\n   146→}\n   147→```\n   148→\n   149→**Note on `createLineProcessor`:** The line-splitting logic (buffering partial lines across chunk boundaries, splitting on `\\n`) is generic and useful. It can stay in `run-helpers.ts` as a utility OR be inlined in run.ts. The key change is that `createLineProcessor`'s internal calls to `parseStreamLine()` and `parseRalphMessage()` are replaced by `driver.parseOutput()`.\n   150→\n   151→**Ralph existence check:** Currently run.ts does `if (!existsSync(ralphPath))`. After migration, the driver should handle this. Options:\n   152→- Add a `validate(): boolean` method to `AgentDriver` interface\n   153→- Have `driver.spawn()` throw if the executable is missing\n   154→- Keep a lightweight check in run.ts that asks the driver for its executable path\n   155→\n   156→The simplest approach: let `driver.spawn()` throw with a descriptive error if ralph.sh is missing. run.ts catches the error in its existing try/catch.\n   157→\n   158→### Testing Guidance\n   159→\n   160→- **Vitest** (not Jest). Use `vi.fn()`, `vi.mock()`, `vi.mocked()`.\n   161→- Import convention: use `.js` extension for ESM resolution.\n   162→- The run.test.ts mock strategy shifts from mocking `node:child_process.spawn` to mocking `agents/index.js.getDriver()`. The mock driver returns a mock `AgentProcess` with controllable stdout/stderr emitters.\n   163→- Test that `handleAgentEvent()` correctly dispatches each `AgentEvent` type to the renderer.\n   164→- Existing tests for `buildSpawnArgs` in `run-helpers.test.ts` and `ralph.test.ts` are NOT affected — they test the ralph module directly.\n   165→\n   166→### Previous Story Intelligence (13-2)\n   167→\n   168→- Story 13-2 completed. `RalphDriver` exists at `src/lib/agents/ralph.ts` with `spawn()`, `parseOutput()`, `getStatusFile()`.\n   169→- `RalphDriver.spawn()` currently hardcodes `maxIterations: 50`, `iterationTimeout: 30`, `calls: 100`, `quiet: false`. These need to become configurable (Task 1).\n   170→- `createLineProcessor` in `run-helpers.ts` still imports from `agents/ralph.js` — it's the bridge between old and new patterns.\n   171→- `run.ts` currently re-exports `buildSpawnArgs` and `resolveRalphPath` from line 22. Tests import these from `run.ts`. After migration, tests should import directly from `agents/ralph.js`.\n   172→\n   173→### Project Structure After This Story\n   174→\n   175→```\n   176→src/commands/run.ts              # Refactored: uses AgentDriver interface only\n   177→src/lib/agents/\n   178→├── types.ts                     # AgentDriver, SpawnOpts, AgentProcess, AgentEvent (from 13-1)\n   179→├── ralph.ts                     # RalphDriver with configurable spawn (updated)\n   180→├── stream-parser.ts             # Unchanged (from 13-2)\n   181→├── ralph-prompt.ts              # Unchanged (from 13-2)\n   182→├── index.ts                     # Updated: adds getDriver() factory\n   183→└── __tests__/\n   184→    ├── types.test.ts            # From 13-1\n   185→    ├── ralph.test.ts            # From 13-2\n   186→    ├── stream-parser.test.ts    # From 13-2\n   187→    └── ralph-prompt.test.ts     # From 13-2\n   188→src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts  # Updated: mocks AgentDriver instead of child_process\n   189→src/lib/run-helpers.ts              # Possibly trimmed: createLineProcessor may be removed\n   190→```\n   191→\n   192→### References\n   193→\n   194→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v3.md Decision 3] — Agent Abstraction specification\n   195→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-architecture-v3.md lines 291-305] — Story 13-3 epic definition\n   196→- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/13-1-agentdriver-interface-and-types.md] — Story 13-1 completion notes\n   197→- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/13-2-ralph-driver-implementation.md] — Story 13-2 completion notes\n   198→- [Source: src/commands/run.ts] — Primary file to refactor\n   199→- [Source: src/lib/agents/ralph.ts] — RalphDriver implementation to extend\n   200→- [Source: src/lib/agents/index.ts] — Barrel to add getDriver() factory\n   201→- [Source: src/lib/run-helpers.ts] — createLineProcessor to potentially remove\n   202→\n   203→## File List\n   204→\n   205→- `src/commands/run.ts` — Refactor: replace direct spawn/buildSpawnArgs/resolveRalphPath with AgentDriver interface\n   206→- `src/lib/agents/index.ts` — Add `getDriver()` factory function\n   207→- `src/lib/agents/ralph.ts` — Extend `RalphDriver.spawn()` to accept full configuration\n   208→- `src/lib/agents/types.ts` — Possibly add `RalphSpawnOpts` or constructor config type\n   209→- `src/lib/run-helpers.ts` — Possibly remove `createLineProcessor` if no longer needed\n   210→- `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` — Update mocks from child_process to AgentDriver\n   211→\n   212→## Change Log\n   213→\n   214→- 2026-03-24: Story created by /create-story\n   215→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AeYymucNLjmuqL83DiV485","session_id":"a5a043ae-cfd1-4d51-82dd-d0069edc63ef","uuid":"3e24787e-f617-41fc-8982-f125e7e0026b","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:30:22.335Z"}
