{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AeYymucNLjmuqL83DiV485","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is the review summary:\n\n**Adversarial review of story 13-3 complete.** Two issues found and fixed:\n\n1. **MEDIUM (fixed):** `src/lib/agents/index.ts` had 0% test coverage. The `getDriver()` factory function — the core deliverable of AC6 — was completely untested. Created `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/agents/__tests__/index.test.ts` with 5 tests covering: default driver, named driver, config passthrough, unknown driver error, and error message content. Coverage now 100%.\n\n2. **MEDIUM (fixed):** `src/commands/run.ts` line 283 had hardcoded `\"Failed to start Ralph\"` error message, violating the agent-agnostic principle that is the entire point of this story. Changed to `\"Failed to start agent\"`. Updated corresponding test assertion in `run.test.ts`.\n\n**Verification results:**\n- Build: passes (zero errors)\n- Tests: 137 files, all passing (zero regressions)\n- Coverage: 97.08% overall (target: 90%), all 153 files above 80% floor\n- Line counts: all files under 300 lines (run.ts=287, ralph.ts=287)\n- All 13 acceptance criteria verified\n\n**Files modified:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/run.ts` — fixed hardcoded agent name in error message\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` — updated error message assertion\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/agents/__tests__/index.test.ts` — created (new file)\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/13-3-migrate-run-ts-to-agentdriver.md` — status changed to `verifying`\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and fixed:**\n- MEDIUM: `getDriver()` factory (AC6) had zero test coverage — entire function was mocked away in run.test.ts, and no dedicated test existed\n- MEDIUM: Hardcoded \"Failed to start Ralph\" error message in agent-agnostic `run.ts` — should not reference a specific agent name\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority):**\n- LOW: `getDriver()` factory signature accepts `config?: RalphConfig` — coupling the generic factory to a ralph-specific type. When a second driver is added, this will need refactoring to a union config type or per-driver config strategy\n- LOW: `handleAgentEvent()` uses `event as Parameters<RendererHandle['update']>[0]` type assertion (line 36) — masks potential type mismatches between `AgentEvent` and `StreamEvent` shapes\n- LOW: `run.ts` and `ralph.ts` are both at 287 lines — 13 lines from the 300-line limit. Any future additions risk exceeding the ceiling\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- `run.ts` at 93.65% statements — uncovered lines 103, 149-152 (prompt write error path), 263 (status file parse error). These are error-handling paths that would benefit from explicit error-path tests\n- `run-helpers.ts` `createLineProcessor` (lines 110-141) is no longer used by `run.ts` but still exists and is partially covered. It's dead code from `run.ts`'s perspective\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- `createLineProcessor` in `run-helpers.ts` still imports from `agents/ralph.js` and duplicates parsing logic that now lives inside `RalphDriver.parseOutput()`. It should be deprecated or removed if no external consumers depend on it\n- The `RalphConfig` type is exported from both `ralph.ts` and `index.ts` barrel — consumers may import from either path, creating two entry points for the same type\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All issues found were fixed in this session."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ae7d6a73f823cb155 (use SendMessage with to: 'ae7d6a73f823cb155' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 54171\ntool_uses: 33\nduration_ms: 261295</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a5a043ae-cfd1-4d51-82dd-d0069edc63ef","uuid":"9acabfd8-a506-404b-a16f-37f729ab88c7","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:34:39.234Z","tool_use_re