r used by `run.ts` but still exists and is partially covered. It's dead code from `run.ts`'s perspective\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- `createLineProcessor` in `run-helpers.ts` still imports from `agents/ralph.js` and duplicates parsing logic that now lives inside `RalphDriver.parseOutput()`. It should be deprecated or removed if no external consumers depend on it\n- The `RalphConfig` type is exported from both `ralph.ts` and `index.ts` barrel — consumers may import from either path, creating two entry points for the same type\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All issues found were fixed in this session."}],"totalDurationMs":261295,"totalTokens":54171,"totalToolUseCount":33,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":336,"cache_read_input_tokens":52856,"output_tokens":978,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":336},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
