ompleted |\n  1860→|-------|------|---------|--------------------------|\n  1861→| 11-3-state-reconciliation-on-session-start | Epic 11 | done | create-story, dev-story (from earlier in day) |\n  1862→| 12-1-split-coverage-ts-domain-subdirectory | Epic 12 | done | create-story, dev-story, code-review, verification |\n  1863→| 12-2-split-docker-otlp-beads-dochealth | Epic 12 | done | create-story, dev-story, code-review |\n  1864→| 12-3-move-status-logic-to-module | Epic 12 | done | dev-story, code-review |\n  1865→| 12-4-shared-test-utilities-fixtures | Epic 12 | done | create-story, dev-story, code-review, verification |\n  1866→| 13-1-agentdriver-interface-and-types | Epic 13 | done | create-story, dev-story (implicit), code-review, verification |\n  1867→| 13-2-ralph-driver-implementation | Epic 13 | ready-for-dev | create-story, dev-story (started) |\n  1868→\n  1869→**Net progress:** Epic 12 fully closed (all 4 stories done). Epic 13 started — 1 of 3 stories done, 13-2 dev complete but not yet reviewed/verified, 13-3 remains in backlog.\n  1870→\n  1871→**Commits:** 6 story commits + 1 epic-complete commit landed on master.\n  1872→\n  1873→---\n  1874→\n  1875→## 2. Issues Analysis\n  1876→\n  1877→### Bugs Discovered During Implementation or Verification\n  1878→\n  1879→| Severity | Story | Issue | Fixed? |\n  1880→|----------|-------|-------|--------|\n  1881→| HIGH | 12-1 | runner.ts statement coverage at 78.15% (below 80% floor) | Yes — added 11 tests, raised to 95.79% |\n  1882→| HIGH | 12-2 | docker/cleanup.ts had 0% coverage | Yes — added cleanup.test.ts |\n  1883→| HIGH | 12-2 | observability/backends.ts had 0% coverage | Yes — added backends.test.ts |\n  1884→| MEDIUM | 12-3 | Unused imports (`isSharedStackRunning`, `DockerHealthResult`) left in formatters.ts after extraction | Yes — removed |\n  1885→| MEDIUM | 12-3 | Missing mock for `modules/verify/index.js` in status.test.ts | Yes — added mock |\n  1886→| MEDIUM | 12-4 | `createStateMock()` exported phantom functions `readLocalConfig` and `getProjectRoot` that don't exist | Yes — split into `createStateMock()` and `createSprintStateMock()` |\n  1887→| MEDIUM | 12-4 | Unused `StoryStatus` type import in state-builders.ts | Yes — removed |\n  1888→\n  1889→### Workarounds Applied (Tech Debt Introduced)\n  1890→\n  1891→| Story | Workaround | Debt Description |\n  1892→|-------|-----------|-----------------|\n  1893→| 11-3 | JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(...)) deep clone for Readonly mutation | Proper immutable state update pattern needed |\n  1894→| 12-2 | Circular dependency in doc-health resolved by extracting shared utils to types.ts | Extra file not in original story spec; fragile coupling |\n  1895→| 12-2 | cleanup.ts and backends.ts are placeholder stubs, not real implementations | Stub code will need to be replaced when functionality is built |\n  1896→| 12-2 | Test files kept as monolithic files moved to `__tests__/` dirs instead of split per-module | AC10 partially addressed — functional but not ideal |\n  1897→| 13-1 | Created `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/AGENTS.md` to work around `checkAgentsMdForModule` fallback logic | Masking a real bug in the staleness checker |\n  1898→| 13-2 | `RalphDriver.spawn()` hardcodes defaults (maxIterations: 50, iterationTimeout: 30) | SpawnOpts doesn't carry ralph-specific options; deferred to 13-3 |\n  1899→| 13-2 | `parseOutput()` maps retry events with `delay: 0` | Ralph stderr doesn't include delay info; incomplete data |\n  1900→\n  1901→### Code Quality Concerns\n  1902→\n  1903→| Severity | Story | Concern |\n  1904→|----------|-------|---------|\n  1905→| LOW | 12-1 | `findCoverageSummary` exported from parser.ts but not from index.ts barrel — only used as sibling import |\n  1906→| LOW | 12-2 | doc-health/index.ts leaks internal utility functions through barrel |\n  1907→| LOW | 12-2 | doc-health/types.ts duplicates SOURCE_EXTENSIONS constant (3 copies) |\n  1908→| LOW | 12-2 | staleness.ts at 284 lines — close to 300-line limit |\n  1909→| LOW | 12-3 | No dedicated unit tests for formatters.ts or drill-down.ts at module level |\n  1910→| LOW | 12-3 | `printSprintState()` and `handleFullStatusJson()` independently call report generation — duplication |\n  1911→| LOW | 12-4 | selector.test.ts wraps shared builders in local helpers rather than using `buildSprintState` directly |\n  1912→| LOW | 12-4 | No `index.ts` barrel file in `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/` |\n  1913→| LOW | 13-1 | `Function` type used in mock — may trigger eslint ban-types rule |\n  1914→| LOW | 13-1 | `createMockProcess()` mock stores handlers but never exposes them for invocation |\n  1915→\n  1916→### Verification Gaps\n  1917→\n  1918→| Story | Gap |\n  1919→|-------|-----|\n  1920→| 12-1 | AC11 (integration-required) escalated — needs Docker for CLI behavior identity testing; Docker Desktop was not running |\n  1921→| 12-1 | `codeharness coverage --check-only` misparses test counts as \"0 passed, 0 failed\" |\n  1922→| 12-3 | `getValidationProgress` integration path only implicitly tested |\n  1923→| 12-4 | Mock factories cannot be used inside `vi.mock()` due to Vitest hoisting — pattern's value limited |\n  1924→| 13-1 | Beads sync failed — story file status line not found (parsing issue) |\n  1925→\n  1926→### Tooling/Infrastructure Problems\n  1927→\n  1928→| Story | Problem |\n  1929→|-------|---------|\n  1930→| 12-1 | Docker Desktop daemon not running — blocked black-box verification for ~100 seconds before timeout |\n  1931→| 12-1 | `codeharness verify` precondition check requires `tests_passed` session flag — had to run `codeharness coverage` first |\n  1932→| 12-1 | Proof format issue: initial proof used plain ``` blocks but parser requires ```bash + ```output pairs |\n  1933→| 12-4 | Proof initially failed: missing `**Tier:** unit-testable` header required by `validateProofQuality()` |\n  1934→| 13-1 | AGENTS.md staleness checker falls back to root AGENTS.md instead of `src/lib/AGENTS.md` |\n  1935→| All | Pre-existing ~60-80 type errors in unrelated test files (not introduced this session) |\n  1936→\n  1937→---\n  1938→\n  1939→## 3. What Went Well\n  1940→\n  1941→- **Epic 12 completed in a single session** — all 4 domain subdirectory refactoring stories done, reviewed, and verified. This was the largest refactoring epic: coverage.ts (633 lines), docker.ts, otlp.ts, beads.ts, doc-health.ts (832 lines), and status logic all decomposed into domain subdirectories.\n  1942→- **Code review caught real bugs every time** — runner.ts coverage gap (78%), phantom mock functions, unused imports, 0% coverage files. The review stage consistently adds value.\n  1943→- **Epic 13 types story (13-1) was clean** — no HIGH or MEDIUM issues found during review. Types-only stories are low-risk and fast.\n  1944→- **Test suite grew significantly** — from ~3,539 tests to 3,600+ with zero regressions across all stories.\n  1945→- **Coverage stayed above 97%** — 97.09% overall at session end, all 152 files above 80% floor.\n  1946→- **Story 12-4 established shared test utilities** — `buildSprintState()`, `buildStoryEntry()`, mock factories now available for all future test files.\n  1947→- **13-2 dev completed with all 3,600+ Vitest tests and 307 BATS tests passing** — large migration (RalphDriver, stream-parser move) with zero regressions.\n  1948→\n  1949→---\n  1950→\n  1951→## 4. What Went Wrong\n  1952→\n  1953→- **Docker Desktop down** — blocked 12-1 verification. AC11 (integration-required) had to be escalated rather than verified. No one noticed until the verifier tried to run it.\n  1954→- **Pre-existing type errors** — ~60-80 TS errors in test files reported by multiple subagents. Not blockers (tests still pass via Vitest), but noise that obscures real issues. Tracked as story 15-4 in backlog.\n  1955→- **vi.mock() hoisting limitation** — 12-4's mock factory pattern can't be used inside `vi.mock()` callbacks due to Vitest hoisting. This fundamentally limits the pattern's value. The story's dev notes example \"doesn't work as written.\"\n  1956→- **YAML regeneration on every state write** — 11-3 identified that `writeStateAtomic()` always regenerates sprint-status.yaml even when nothing changed. Minor perf issue but wasteful.\n  1957→- **Proof format strictness** — multiple stories hit validation failures because proof format requirements (tier headers, bash+output block pairs) are not well documented. Subagents waste cycles re-formatting proofs.\n  1958→- **Epic numbering confusion** — epic-12-retrospective.md describes a different Epic 12 (verification pipeline integrity) from the actual Epic 12 (domain subdirectory refactoring). Numbering was reused after renumbering.\n  1959→- **13-2 create-story expanded from 2 to 16 ACs** — epic-level ACs were too terse. AC expansion is necessary but means epic estimates are unreliable.\n  1960→\n  1961→---\n  1962→\n  1963→## 5. Lessons Learned\n  1964→\n  1965→### Patterns to Repeat\n  1966→\n  1967→1. **Code review as a gate works** — every story had issues caught at review that would have shipped otherwise. Keep the review stage mandatory.\n  1968→2. **Domain subdirectory pattern is solid** — 12-1 established it, 12-2/12-3/12-4 followed. Consistent file organization across all domains now.\n  1969→3. **Types-only stories are fast and clean** — 13-1 had no HIGH/MEDIUM issues. Separate type stories from implementation stories when possible.\n  1970→4. **Running full test suite after each story** — caught regressions early. Zero regressions across 7 stories.\n  1971→\n  1972→### Patterns to Avoid\n  1973→\n  1974→1. **Don't write dev notes examples that rely on Vitest hoisting** — `vi.mock()` callback cannot reference imported symbols. Document this limitation in shared test utilities.\n  1975→2. **Don't assume Docker is running** — verifier should check Docker availability before attempting integration-required ACs, not after 100 seconds of waiting.\n  1976→3. **Don't rely on epic-level ACs** — they're consistently too terse (2 ACs expanded to 10-16). Budget time for AC expansion at story creation.\n  1977→4. **Don't skip barrel re-exports** — `findCoverageSummary` in parser.ts, no barrel in fixtures/ — these gaps accumulate.\n  1978→\n  1979→---\n  1980→\n  1981→## 6. Action Items\n  1982→\n  1983→### Fix Now (Before Next Session)\n  1984→\n  1985→| Action | Source |\n  1986→|--------|--------|\n  1987→| Review and merge 13-2 (code-review + verification pending) | 13-2 is dev-complete but not through the full pipeline |\n  1988→| Ensure Docker Desktop is running before next autonomous session | 12-1 verification blocker |\n  1989→\n  1990→### Fix Soon (Next Sprint)\n  1991→\n  1992→| Action | Source |\n  1993→|--------|--------|\n  1994→| Fix `checkAgentsMdForModule` fallback logic — should resolve to nearest AGENTS.md, not root | 13-1 verification workaround |\n  1995→| Fix `codeharness coverage --check-only` test count parsing (\"0 passed, 0 failed\") | 12-1 verification tooling bug |\n  1996→| Document proof format requirements (tier headers, bash+output pairs) for subagents | 12-1, 12-4 verification friction |\n  1997→| Add Docker availability pre-check to `codeharness verify` before integration-required ACs | 12-1 verification blocker |\n  1998→| Fix `parseStoryKey()` returning `[Infinity, Infinity]` for non-matching keys | 11-3 identified risk |\n  1999→| Add dedicated unit tests for formatters.ts and drill-down.ts | 12-3 review gap |\n  2000→| Export `findCoverageSummary` from coverage/index.ts barrel | 12-1 review finding |\n  2001→| Deduplicate SOURCE_EXTENSIONS constant (3 copies in doc-health) | 12-2 review finding |\n  2002→| Document vi.mock() hoisting limitation in shared test utilities README | 12-4 lesson learned |\n  2003→\n  2004→### Backlog (Track But Not Urgent)\n  2005→\n  2006→| Action | Source |\n  2007→|--------|--------|\n  2008→| Fix pre-existing ~60-80 TS type errors in test files (story 15-4) | Multiple stories |\n  