 | Circular dependency in doc-health resolved by extracting shared utilities to doc-health/types.ts (extra file not in story spec) | Low |\n  2076→| 12-2 | beads.ts 300-line limit forced moving types/functions to story-files.ts (story specified them in beads.ts) | Low |\n  2077→| 12-2 | cleanup.ts and backends.ts are placeholder stubs — real logic lives elsewhere | Medium |\n  2078→| 13-1 | Created `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/AGENTS.md` to work around `checkAgentsMdForModule` fallback logic gap | Low |\n  2079→| 13-2 | `retry` event maps `delay: 0` — ralph stderr doesn't include delay info | Low |\n  2080→| 13-2 | `RalphDriver.spawn()` hardcodes maxIterations/iterationTimeout/calls — SpawnOpts needs expansion in 13-3 | Medium |\n  2081→| 13-3 | AgentEvent-to-StreamEvent type cast — shapes match structurally but no formal type relationship | Medium |\n  2082→| 13-3 | `storyKey: ''` passed to driver.spawn() — SpawnOpts requires it but run.ts lacks single story key | Medium |\n  2083→| 11-3 | Readonly mutation uses JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(...)) deep clone + type assertions | Low |\n  2084→\n  2085→### Code Quality Concerns\n  2086→\n  2087→| Severity | Story | Concern |\n  2088→|----------|-------|---------|\n  2089→| LOW | 12-1 | `findCoverageSummary` exported from parser.ts but not from index.ts barrel (sibling-only usage) |\n  2090→| LOW | 12-2 | doc-health/index.ts leaks internal utility functions through barrel |\n  2091→| LOW | 12-2 | doc-health/types.ts has SOURCE_EXTENSIONS constant duplicated 3 times |\n  2092→| LOW | 12-2 | staleness.ts at 284 lines, close to 300-line limit |\n  2093→| LOW | 12-3 | No dedicated unit tests for formatters.ts or drill-down.ts |\n  2094→| LOW | 12-3 | `printSprintState()` and `handleFullStatusJson()` independently call report generation (potential duplication) |\n  2095→| LOW | 12-4 | selector.test.ts wraps shared builders in local helpers rather than using `buildSprintState` directly |\n  2096→| LOW | 12-4 | No `index.ts` barrel file in `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/` |\n  2097→| LOW | 13-1 | `createMockProcess()` stores handlers but never exposes them for invocation |\n  2098→| LOW | 13-2 | `resolveRalphPath()` uses fragile `endsWith('/src')` check |\n  2099→| LOW | 13-2 | `retry` event drops story key — AgentEvent.retry has no `key` field |\n  2100→| LOW | 13-3 | `createLineProcessor` still exists in run-helpers.ts, unused by run.ts, imports from agents/ralph.js |\n  2101→\n  2102→### Verification Gaps\n  2103→\n  2104→| Story | Gap |\n  2105→|-------|-----|\n  2106→| 12-1 | AC11 (integration-required) escalated — needs Docker for CLI behavior identity testing |\n  2107→| 12-1 | Docker Desktop daemon not running — blocked all black-box verification |\n  2108→| 12-1 | `codeharness coverage --check-only` misparses test counts as \"0 passed, 0 failed\" |\n  2109→| 12-2 | Test files not reorganized per AC10 (monolithic test files moved as-is) |\n  2110→| 12-3 | `getValidationProgress` integration path only implicitly tested |\n  2111→| 13-1 | Beads sync failed — story file status line not found (parsing issue) |\n  2112→| 13-3 | Not yet verified — still in review |\n  2113→\n  2114→### Tooling/Infrastructure Problems\n  2115→\n  2116→| Story | Problem |\n  2117→|-------|---------|\n  2118→| 12-1 | Docker Desktop not running, `open -a Docker` didn't start within 100s — blocked black-box verification |\n  2119→| 12-1 | `codeharness verify` precondition requires `tests_passed` session flag — had to run `codeharness coverage` first |\n  2120→| 12-1 | Proof format issue: parser requires ```bash + ```output pairs, not plain ``` blocks |\n  2121→| 12-4 | Proof initially failed validation: missing `**Tier:** unit-testable` header |\n  2122→| 12-1 | Workflow file was `workflow.yaml` not `workflow.md` — skill invocation message referenced wrong extension |\n  2123→| All | Pre-existing ~60-80 TS type errors in unrelated test files (not introduced this session) |\n  2124→| 12-4 | vi.mock() hoisting prevents using imported factory functions inside vi.mock() callbacks — fundamental Vitest limitation |\n  2125→\n  2126→---\n  2127→\n  2128→## 3. What Went Well\n  2129→\n  2130→- **Epic 12 fully closed** — all 4 domain subdirectory refactoring stories completed with code review fixes applied. Established the `src/lib/{domain}/` pattern for future use.\n  2131→- **Epic 13 making strong progress** — 2 of 3 stories done, the AgentDriver interface and RalphDriver are landed. Migration story (13-3) through dev.\n  2132→- **Code review catching real bugs** — every code review found at least one HIGH or MEDIUM issue. The 0% coverage catches on cleanup.ts and backends.ts prevented shipping untested stubs.\n  2133→- **Coverage maintained above 97%** across 152+ files despite significant file restructuring (moves, splits, new modules).\n  2134→- **Test count growth** — 3,600+ Vitest tests + 307 BATS tests, up from previous sessions. New test utilities (state-builders, mock factories) accelerating test authoring.\n  2135→- **Circular dependency in doc-health resolved cleanly** — the types.ts extraction was not in the story spec but was the right architectural call.\n  2136→\n  2137→---\n  2138→\n  2139→## 4. What Went Wrong\n  2140→\n  2141→- **Docker Desktop unavailability** blocked all black-box/integration verification for the entire session. AC11 on story 12-1 remains escalated with no resolution path attempted beyond `open -a Docker`.\n  2142→- **Pre-existing ~80 TS type errors** in test files create noise in every story. These are mock type annotation gaps — not real bugs — but they make it harder to verify \"zero new type errors\" claims.\n  2143→- **vi.mock() hoisting limitation** undermines the value of shared mock factories (story 12-4). The pattern works for `vi.mocked()` return value configuration but not for `vi.mock()` declarations, which is where most test boilerplate lives.\n  2144→- **Story specs diverge from reality** — multiple stories required AC expansion from 2 to 10-16 ACs. Epic-level AC definitions are too terse to guide implementation. The create-story agent does good work expanding them, but it burns a full pipeline stage on what should be upfront planning.\n  2145→- **Stub modules shipped** — cleanup.ts and backends.ts are essentially empty placeholders with tests that verify they export the right shape. Real logic lives elsewhere. This is tech debt that looks like progress.\n  2146→- **13-3 type casting** between AgentEvent and StreamEvent is a design smell. The two type systems overlap but have no formal relationship, requiring unsafe casts at the boundary.\n  2147→\n  2148→---\n  2149→\n  2150→## 5. Lessons Learned\n  2151→\n  2152→### Patterns to Repeat\n  2153→\n  2154→1. **Code review before verification** — catching 0% coverage files before they enter the verification pipeline saved verification agent time and prevented false completions.\n  2155→2. **AC expansion at create-story time** — terse epic ACs expanded to 10-16 ACs gave dev agents clear targets. Worth the extra pipeline stage.\n  2156→3. **Domain subdirectory pattern** — the `{domain}/index.ts` + `{domain}/types.ts` + `{domain}/__tests__/` structure established in Epic 12 is clean and reusable.\n  2157→4. **Shared test fixtures** — state-builders.ts and mock factories reduce test authoring friction, even with the vi.mock() limitation.\n  2158→\n  2159→### Patterns to Avoid\n  2160→\n  2161→1. **Shipping stub modules as \"done\"** — cleanup.ts and backends.ts should have been flagged as incomplete rather than passing code review with 0% coverage fixes that test stubs.\n  2162→2. **Ignoring Docker availability** — should check Docker status as a session precondition and either start it or mark integration ACs as blocked upfront.\n  2163→3. **Hardcoding values in driver implementations** — RalphDriver.spawn() hardcoding maxIterations/iterationTimeout creates immediate tech debt that 13-3 must clean up.\n  2164→4. **Overwriting existing story files** — story 12-4 overwrote a partial story file with Epic 13 references. Always check for existing content before overwriting.\n  2165→\n  2166→---\n  2167→\n  2168→## 6. Action Items\n  2169→\n  2170→### Fix Now (Before Next Session)\n  2171→\n  2172→| Item | Source | Owner |\n  2173→|------|--------|-------|\n  2174→| Complete 13-3 code review and verification | Sprint status shows \"review\" | Next session |\n  2175→| Start Docker Desktop before next session | Blocked 12-1 AC11 verification | User/infra |\n  2176→| Fix pre-existing TS type errors in test mocks (~80 errors) | Reported in 13-2, 11-3 | Story 15-4 (exists in backlog) |\n  2177→\n  2178→### Fix Soon (Next Sprint)\n  2179→\n  2180→| Item | Source | Owner |\n  2181→|------|--------|-------|\n  2182→| Replace cleanup.ts and backends.ts stubs with real implementations | 12-2 code review | Epic 14 scope |\n  2183→| Formalize AgentEvent-to-StreamEvent type relationship | 13-3 dev issues | Epic 13 cleanup |\n  2184→| Expand SpawnOpts to carry agent-specific config (replace hardcoded values) | 13-2, 13-3 issues | Story 13-3 or follow-up |\n  2185→| Add barrel file for `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/` | 12-4 code review | Minor cleanup |\n  2186→| Deduplicate SOURCE_EXTENSIONS constant (3 copies in doc-health) | 12-2 code review | Tech debt |\n  2187→| Fix `codeharness coverage --check-only` misparsing test counts | 12-1 verification | CLI bug |\n  2188→| Fix beads sync story file status line parsing | 13-1 verification | Tooling bug |\n  2189→\n  2190→### Backlog (Track But Not Urgent)\n  2191→\n  2192→| Item | Source |\n  2193→|------|--------|\n  2194→| Investigate vi.mock() alternatives for shared mock factory adoption | 12-4 architecture concern |\n  2195→| Add `getValidationProgress` integration tests | 12-3 coverage gap |\n  2196→| Add dedicated unit tests for formatters.ts and drill-down.ts | 12-3 code review |\n  2197→| Resolve `createLineProcessor` — remove or migrate | 13-2, 13-3 reverse dependency |\n  2198→| Fix `checkAgentsMdForModule` fallback logic for nested directories | 13-1 workaround |\n  2199→| Refactor `printSprintState` / `handleFullStatusJson` report generation duplication | 12-3 code review |\n  2200→\n  2201→---\n  2202→\n  2203→## Session Metrics\n  2204→\n  2205→| Metric | Value |\n  2206→|--------|-------|\n  2207→| Stories completed this session | 7 done + 1 in review |\n  2208→| Epics closed this session | 2 (Epic 11, Epic 12) |\n  2209→| Total stories done in sprint | 52 of 66 |\n  2210→| Sprint completion | 78.8% |\n  2211→| HIGH issues found by code review | 4 (all fixed) |\n  2212→| MEDIUM issues found by code review | 7 (all fixed) |\n  2213→| LOW issues (unfixed, tracked) | 12 |\n  2214→| Verification gaps (escalated ACs) | 1 (12-1 AC11 integration-required) |\n  2215→| Test count at session end | 3,600+ Vitest + 307 BATS |\n  2216→| Coverage at session end | 97.08% overall, 153 files above 80% floor |\n  2217→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01RtADB7CuMpFEzwitbvaZxk","session_id":"a5a043ae-cfd1-4d51-82dd-d0069edc63ef","uuid":"9629dd75-caea-4d9e-8983-02c7e319e048","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:38:56.868Z"}
